    <h2>1. Sinmag — The Indian Market's Workhorse</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Taiwan | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1978 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Since early 2000s</p>
    <p>Sinmag is arguably the most popular imported bakery equipment brand in India by volume. Walk into any mid-range Indian bakery and the odds are good you'll find a Sinmag oven, mixer, or proofer. The reason is simple: they offer reliable, well-built equipment at prices that are significantly below European competitors.</p>
    <p>Sinmag's convection ovens, deck ovens, and spiral mixers are particularly well-regarded. Their equipment isn't the cheapest (Indian brands undercut them), and it's not the most sophisticated (European brands beat them there), but in the middle ground they occupy a dominant position. Build quality is good, temperature accuracy is solid, and the machines tend to last.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Deck ovens, convection ovens, spiral dough mixers, bread proofers</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sinmag 4-tray convection oven: ₹75,000 – ₹1,10,000</li>
      <li>Sinmag 2-deck oven: ₹1,60,000 – ₹2,40,000</li>
      <li>Sinmag spiral mixer (20kg): ₹1,20,000 – ₹1,80,000</li>
      <li>Sinmag rotary rack oven: ₹5,00,000 – ₹8,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Excellent. Authorised distributors in Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Chennai, Pune, and most Tier-2 cities. Multiple importers carry Sinmag products.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Good. Spare parts are readily available through distributors. Most major cities have technicians familiar with Sinmag equipment. AMC (Annual Maintenance Contracts) available.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Sinmag:</strong> Any bakery wanting a step up from Indian brands without paying European prices. Ideal for serious mid-scale operations with a budget of ₹1L–₹10L per equipment item.</p>

    <h2>2. Berjaya — Southeast Asian Value Play</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Malaysia | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1984 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Growing since 2010s</p>
    <p>Berjaya is Malaysia's largest food equipment manufacturer and a major name across Southeast Asia. In India, they're best known for their bakery display cases, ovens, and food warming equipment — primarily targeting café chains, QSR (Quick Service Restaurant) operators, and modern bakery retail.</p>
    <p>Their equipment is a slight notch below Sinmag in build quality but is competitively priced. For bakeries where aesthetics matter — like display cases and front-of-house equipment — Berjaya often wins on looks and price. Their convection ovens are solid performers for standard bakery products.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Bakery display cases, countertop convection ovens, food warmers, soft serve machines</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Berjaya countertop convection oven (4-tray): ₹55,000 – ₹85,000</li>
      <li>Berjaya bakery display case (1.5m): ₹80,000 – ₹1,40,000</li>
      <li>Berjaya commercial refrigerator: ₹60,000 – ₹1,20,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Moderate. Strongest presence in South India (Kerala, Tamil Nadu) and Maharashtra. Distribution has expanded but remains uneven in North India.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Adequate in South India and Maharashtra. Patchy in North and East India — verify service availability in your city before buying.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Berjaya:</strong> Cafés and bakery-cafés wanting good-looking display equipment at reasonable prices, particularly in southern states.</p>

    <h2>3. Salva — Spanish Precision for Bread Bakers</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Spain | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1943 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Since 2010s</p>
    <p>Salva is one of Spain's oldest and most respected bakery equipment manufacturers. Their deck ovens are regarded among the best in the world for artisan bread baking, with excellent heat retention, accurate temperature control, and robust steam injection systems. They also make quality proofers, spiral mixers, and dividers.</p>
    <p>In India, Salva equipment is imported by a few specialist dealers and is found mainly in artisan bakeries, 5-star hotel bakeries, and bakery schools. The brand is less well-known among general bakery equipment buyers, but those who have used Salva equipment tend to be loyal customers.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Deck ovens, bread proofers, spiral mixers, bread dividers/rounders</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Salva 2-deck oven with steam: ₹3,00,000 – ₹4,50,000</li>
      <li>Salva 3-deck oven with steam: ₹5,50,000 – ₹8,00,000</li>
      <li>Salva spiral mixer (30kg): ₹3,00,000 – ₹4,00,000</li>
      <li>Salva bread proofer: ₹1,80,000 – ₹3,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Limited — metro cities only (Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru). Requires importing or working with specialist dealers.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Limited. Relies on authorised service agents in metro cities. Adequate for bakeries that maintain their own engineering staff; not ideal for bakeries dependent on quick manufacturer service.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Salva:</strong> Artisan bakeries, hotel bakeries, and large commercial bakeries where bread quality is paramount and you have technical staff.</p>

    <h2>4. Bongard — French Engineering, Industrial Scale</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> France | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1922 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Since 2000s</p>
    <p>Bongard is one of Europe's oldest bakery equipment brands, with over a century of experience building industrial bread lines, tunnel ovens, rotary ovens, and complete turnkey bakery solutions. Their equipment represents the gold standard for large-scale bread production.</p>
    <p>In India, Bongard is primarily found in industrial bread manufacturing facilities, large supermarket in-house bakeries, and premium hotel bakeries. It's not equipment you buy for a neighbourhood bakery — it's for operations producing thousands of loaves per day.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Industrial deck ovens, tunnel ovens, rotary rack ovens, complete bread production lines</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Bongard rack oven: ₹10,00,000 – ₹18,00,000</li>
      <li>Bongard industrial deck oven: ₹8,00,000 – ₹20,00,000+</li>
      <li>Complete turnkey bread line: ₹50,00,000 – ₹2,00,00,000+</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Limited to major metros. Typically handled by specialist industrial food equipment companies. Projects are usually custom-configured.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Project-based service teams. Not suitable for bakeries that need walk-in repair service — but at this scale, you'd have dedicated maintenance staff anyway.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Bongard:</strong> Industrial bread manufacturers, large supermarket chains setting up in-house bakeries, serious large-scale operations.</p>

