    <h2>5. Hobart — The Gold Standard for Mixers</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> USA | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1897 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Long-established</p>
    <p>Hobart is to commercial mixers what Rolls-Royce is to cars — the name that all others are measured against. Their planetary mixers and spiral mixers are found in the world's best bakeries and hotel kitchens. Hobart also makes commercial dishwashers, slicers, and food processors, but it's the mixers that define the brand.</p>
    <p>In India, Hobart is well-established. Their HL series planetary mixers are standard equipment in 5-star hotel kitchens and serious commercial bakeries. The build quality is exceptional — a well-maintained Hobart mixer can run for 20+ years. The price is correspondingly high.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Planetary mixers, spiral mixers, commercial slicers, food processors</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Hobart planetary mixer (20 litre): ₹2,80,000 – ₹3,80,000</li>
      <li>Hobart planetary mixer (40 litre): ₹4,50,000 – ₹6,00,000</li>
      <li>Hobart spiral mixer (40kg): ₹4,00,000 – ₹5,50,000</li>
      <li>Hobart commercial slicer: ₹1,20,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Good. Pan-India distribution through ITW (Illinois Tool Works) and their authorised dealers. Available in all major cities.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Excellent. Hobart has one of the best service networks among foreign bakery equipment brands in India. Trained technicians and genuine spare parts available nationally.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Hobart:</strong> 5-star hotels, upscale restaurant chains, serious commercial bakeries where mixer quality and longevity justify premium pricing.</p>

    <h2>6. Unox — Italian Innovation in Convection Ovens</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Italy | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1990 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Strong since 2010s</p>
    <p>Unox has rapidly become the go-to premium convection oven brand in India's hospitality and bakery sector. Their BAKERTOP and CHEFTOP lines are packed with technology — automatic humidity control, programmable baking profiles, self-cleaning functions, and connectivity features. Italian quality at prices that are high but not Rational-level.</p>
    <p>Their BAKERTOP Mind.Maps™ ovens are particularly impressive: they learn from baking cycles, suggest adjustments, and can be programmed with hundreds of product recipes. For cloud kitchens, hotel bakeries, and modern bakery chains, Unox offers the best technology-to-price ratio in the premium segment.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Convection ovens (BAKERTOP series), combi ovens (CHEFTOP series)</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Unox 4-tray convection oven: ₹1,50,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
      <li>Unox 8-tray convection oven: ₹2,80,000 – ₹4,50,000</li>
      <li>Unox 16-tray convection oven: ₹5,00,000 – ₹8,00,000</li>
      <li>Unox combi oven: ₹4,50,000 – ₹12,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Excellent. Strong distribution network in all metro cities, good coverage in Tier-2 cities. Multiple authorised dealers.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Good. Unox has invested significantly in building an India service infrastructure. Trained technicians in major cities, good spare parts availability.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Unox:</strong> Cloud kitchens, hotel bakeries, modern bakery chains, and operations that want to standardise baking through programmable recipes.</p>

    <h2>7. Rational — German Engineering at the Top of the Market</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Germany | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1973 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Well-established</p>
    <p>Rational makes the world's most advanced combi ovens — machines that can steam, roast, bake, and grill with extraordinary precision. A Rational oven costs more than most bakeries' entire equipment budgets. But for professional kitchens that need one machine to do everything brilliantly, Rational is unmatched.</p>
    <p>In bakery contexts, Rational combi ovens are excellent for: artisan breads requiring precise humidity control, pastries, croissants, Danish pastries, and anything requiring consistent professional results at scale. The iCombi Pro series can run hundreds of product programmes automatically.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Combi-steamers (iCombi Pro, iCombi Classic)</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Rational iCombi Classic (6-tray): ₹7,00,000 – ₹10,00,000</li>
      <li>Rational iCombi Classic (10-tray): ₹10,00,000 – ₹14,00,000</li>
      <li>Rational iCombi Pro (6-tray): ₹12,00,000 – ₹16,00,000</li>
      <li>Rational iCombi Pro (20-tray): ₹20,00,000 – ₹28,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Excellent. Rational has a direct India presence with sales offices in major cities and a robust network of authorised dealers.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Excellent. Rational is known for exceptional global after-sales service. Trained service engineers in all metro cities, 24-hour helpline, genuine parts.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy Rational:</strong> 5-star hotel restaurants and bakeries, large restaurant chains, premium cloud kitchens, and catering operations where equipment ROI justifies the price.</p>

    <h2>8. WP Bakery Group — German Bakery Machinery</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Germany | <strong>Founded:</strong> 1895 | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Project-based</p>
    <p>WP Bakery Group is one of Europe's largest bakery machinery manufacturers, building everything from industrial dough dividers and rounders to complete tunnel oven systems for industrial bread production. They're not a consumer-facing brand — they build production lines for factories.</p>
    <p>In India, WP equipment is found in industrial bakeries and large bread factories. Like Bongard, they work on project contracts rather than off-the-shelf sales. Equipment is typically configured to the specific production requirements of each customer.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Industrial bread lines, dough dividers, tunnel ovens, rack ovens</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>WP rack oven: ₹12,00,000 – ₹22,00,000</li>
      <li>Industrial bread line (complete): ₹1,00,00,000+</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Project-based. Contact via authorised agents or their German headquarters for India projects.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Project-based engineering support. Not suitable for small/medium bakeries.</p>
    <p><strong>Who should buy WP Bakery:</strong> Industrial bread manufacturers, large supermarket chains, QSR chains with captive bakery production.</p>

    <h2>9. Kolb — Swiss Artisan Bread Equipment</h2>
    <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Switzerland | <strong>India Presence:</strong> Limited specialist importers</p>
    <p>Kolb makes specialised equipment for artisan bread and pastry baking — bread dividers, rounders, sheeters, and moulding equipment designed specifically for artisan and craft bakeries. Swiss precision engineering translates to highly accurate dough handling and minimal product damage.</p>
    <p>In India, Kolb is found primarily in premium artisan bakeries and culinary schools. It's a niche brand — not widely distributed but highly regarded by professional bakers.</p>
    <p><strong>Best equipment:</strong> Dough dividers, bread rounders, baguette moulders, sheeters</p>
    <p><strong>India price range:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Kolb dough divider/rounder: ₹3,50,000 – ₹6,00,000</li>
      <li>Kolb baguette moulder: ₹2,50,000 – ₹4,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>India availability:</strong> Limited. Source through specialist importers in Mumbai or Delhi.</p>
    <p><strong>Service network:</strong> Limited. Best for bakeries with own technical capability.</p>

