    <h2>How to Verify a Brand's India Service Network Before Buying</h2>
    <p>Before committing to any brand, especially an imported one, do these checks:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Ask for the service centre address in your city</strong> — not a phone number, an actual address you can verify.</li>
      <li><strong>Call the service number at an odd hour</strong> — see if it's answered. If it goes straight to voicemail, that tells you something.</li>
      <li><strong>Ask for references</strong> — other bakeries in your city that use the same brand. Call them and ask about service experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Ask about spare parts lead time</strong> — for common wear items like heating elements, thermostats, and door seals. If the answer is "2-3 months from Germany," factor that into your risk assessment.</li>
      <li><strong>Read the AMC terms carefully</strong> — an Annual Maintenance Contract (AMC) is only valuable if the service provider is locally present and responsive.</li>
    </ol>

