    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which is the best bakery equipment brand in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">There's no single "best" brand — it depends on your budget and requirements. For budget buyers, Genius and Ekon (Indian brands) offer good value. For mid-range, Sinmag (Taiwan) is the most popular imported brand with a strong India service network. For premium, Unox (Italy) and Hobart (USA) lead in their respective categories — ovens and mixers. For ultra-premium, Rational (Germany) is the benchmark for combi ovens.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is Sinmag a good brand for Indian bakeries? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — Sinmag is one of the most popular bakery equipment brands in India for good reason. Taiwanese build quality is solid, the price is significantly below European brands, and the India service network is well-developed. Most Indian mid-scale bakeries use Sinmag ovens or mixers. It's the brand we most commonly recommend for bakeries spending ₹1L–₹5L per equipment piece.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is Rational oven worth buying for an Indian bakery? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Rational ovens are worth the price only if you're running a high-volume operation (hotel, large restaurant chain, commercial kitchen) where the equipment will run 8+ hours daily and the cost can be amortised over high production. For a standard Indian neighbourhood bakery, the ROI doesn't work — you'd be paying ₹10–15L for an oven that Sinmag can do for ₹2–3L with less automation but adequate performance.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which brand is best for bakery refrigeration in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For bakery display cases, Celfrost is our top recommendation — best mix of quality, design, and value in India. For general refrigeration (storage, undercounter), Blue Star is the safest choice with its unmatched pan-India service network. For ice machines, Hoshizaki is the gold standard. For premium display cases in modern bakery-cafés, Berjaya and Elanpro are worth considering.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Should I buy Indian brand or imported bakery equipment? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">It depends on your budget and location. If you're in a Tier-2 or Tier-3 city with limited imported brand service, Indian brands (Genius, Ekon, Blue Star, Celfrost) make more sense — you'll get faster repairs and cheaper spares. If you're in a metro city with a bigger budget, Sinmag (mid-range) or Unox/Hobart (premium) are worth the investment for better performance and longevity. Read our guide on <a href="/blog/how-to-buy-bakery-equipment">how to buy bakery equipment</a> for a full framework.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What bakery equipment brands are available in India for small bakeries? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For small bakeries on a tight budget, the best options are: Ekon and Genius for ovens (₹35,000–₹1,40,000), Celfrost for display cases (₹45,000–₹80,000), and Blue Star for refrigeration (₹40,000–₹70,000). Sinmag is worth stretching for if your budget allows — their quality noticeably exceeds entry-level Indian brands. See our <a href="/blog/bakery-oven-price-india">bakery oven price guide</a> for detailed cost breakdowns.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

